ms of architecture, which is the product of computer modelling and algorithmic calculation tools"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-24T23:19:43.000Z","msg":"Parametricism is one of the rising trend these days. But there is an argument whether Parametricism is for nothing / for the sake of being parametric, which is just simply playing with the algorithmic but does not governed by any parameters. <img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/think.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-25T00:04:25.000Z","msg":"yes, what you are mentioning is totally true, but it would be a way more appropriate substitute for replacing futurism and neo futurism as the answer of what is the current trend in architecture, and this is irrelevant to the arguments you mentioned though I deeply agree with that<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\n簡單啲來講可以話啲新嘅電腦同algorithmic 技術來個陣咪有啲cls architect應用左啲技術去起批建築，有人就argue this is the manifestation of post fordism, 但時間一耐太多建築係咁起其實parametric嘅應用同舊建築有咩必然關係<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/wonder2.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />但鳩用parametricism就明顯同賺錢有關係囉<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/point2.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\nnot governed by any paremeters我唔敢講 至少個form or structure係algorithm generate,有冇用 set返parameters去optimize 某啲behaviour我就唔識<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"3798c32b48ae9174c35c09bb04b30c077ddb452a","tid":2076493,"uid":128896,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"d6303dfbdc761e3b6201155656022bcd48163c23","tid":2076493,"uid":104474,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"5430d95373e825bb6d433ba54a69c7d3402bb1ef","tid":2076493,"uid":128896,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"85b556b3b4191b280726e6497719a9dd64ab2edd","tid":2076493,"uid":104474,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-24T22:09:56.000Z","msg":"後現代係咪已經係最新思潮<br />\n有咩書同term 要識<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n除左<br />\nFoucault ,sarte, post-fordism"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-24T22:28:18.000Z","msg":"如果要講出名，應該都係judith butler同foucault嘅理論。<br />\n如果講terms，我會覺得identity、representation同Marxism都係理解後現代嘅重要基礎，最好可以理解埋符號（signifier &amp; signified）。<br />\n<br />\n我才疏學淺，未知後現代係咪最新思潮，不過我見so far學術界主要都係回應/套用90年代左右嘅理論，未聽到有啲咩震驚全世家嘅知名理論，唔少後現代理論家都仲在生添<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/wink.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />。<br />\n<br />\n而我個人推薦lyotard嘅後現代狀況，同埋bauman嘅液態現代性，兩位都比較易睇易明，同埋比較係描述整體現象，唔會因為研究對象太specific而睇唔明<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-24T23:53:20.000Z","msg":"可唔可以elaborate下點樣identity representation Marxism-&gt; postmodern<br />\n<br />\n同埋第3段啲terms<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\n唔知點入手"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-25T00:11:40.000Z","msg":"應該咁講，我認為要讀呢啲抽象野需要唔同嘅context同埋概念幫自己想像究竟樣野討論緊乜，好難好似理科咁一樣一樣學再進攻另一樣野，所以拋咗三個重要基礎concept出黎。<br />\n<br />\nIdentity politics最基本係提出咗身份係被建構出黎，理解咗就會開始觸類旁通，例如會更加理解foucault所講嘅微型權力點樣運作同操控人。建議可以睇下好可愛嘅zizek<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\nrepresentation（再現）同marxism都係同理，好多野其實係再現，而呢種再現好可能又係會影響社會而又好多人唔知。例如愛回家係一種香港家庭生活嘅再現，而呢種再現往往係虛假而塑造同一價值觀，甚至主流價值觀，例如佢會塑造到大學生係冇自理能力嘅廢青。雖然原意可能只係搞笑，但其實都中滲有好多價值，而觀眾睇完，可能會受呢種價值影響。<br />\n<br />\nMarxism就實在好多，你讀熟佢個套思想，再拎過去幾百年嘅社會發展趨勢黎睇，可以好宏觀地了解資本主義有咩問題，同埋佢點樣不斷轉化得更誇張更唔公平，例如新自由主義。讀後現代人嘅毛病好多時都係太離地，完全欠缺歷史觀，變到只係用理論鳩吹一堆野，所以進入呢個領域前最好打好個歷史基礎。<br />\n<br />\n簡單講3個概念都已經好長<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />，第三段係兩個人名嘅兩本書黎，可以直接google/去睇書<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/tongue.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"b1c047cf8223fc8310751d870d3136541012826b","tid":2076493,"uid":128896,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"1b771d6ea0da7d6be37ee77a19137f99eb0ec67f","tid":2076493,"uid":358512,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"92932f45d170bad5483a01f61a44a2f915370d5d","tid":2076493,"uid":128896,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"1a5fba7929